“We cannot believe that you would grant this territory to a state that is foreign to us and that oppresses and destroys minorities and that has in no way contributed to the victory of the Allies without taking into account the opinion of the quarter of a million inhabitants,” the letter reads.
The alleged reason why the authors cannot sign the letter is the fear of the desire for revenge of the "Czech oppressors".
