Although the text contained in the letter may, given the current knowledge of post-war history, seem somewhat naive, according to some survivors, it illustrates well the expectations of the Germans of the Sudeten at the time.
While the Czech Germans had at least to imagine that the question of their expulsion from the republic would arise, very few of them admitted such a possibility.
