Questions that arise after the accident: Are stewards in the bus illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long-distance car is forbidden
In the context of the tragic accident of the bus company Student Agency near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether stewards and passengers can move inside the bus during the journey.
"If we wanted to comply with the law strictly and formally, the activity of a steward is contrary to the road traffic law," said Transport Ministry spokesman Karel Hanzelka.
The accident in question, during which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck who crossed the bus path.
The girl was sadly sitting next to the driver in the most dangerous seat in the vehicle at the time, although she had two other seats at her disposal.
However, the bus may have an accident, or even brake abruptly, even when the steward serves the coffee or distributes the newspapers.
What matters is whether the coach is equipped with standing seats or not under its technical data sheet.
If this stand-up equipment is not approved, passengers shall remain seated.
Student Agency long-distance coaches do not have standing places; this has been confirmed to Aktuáln<0xC4><0x9B>.cz by company director Radim Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura.
"This is an issue that we have dealt with with the ministry and, at the beginning, it prohibits any travel of passengers.
Then they cancelled it and we got passengers to go to the toilet during the ride provided they had their own seat," he said.
The law ignores the steward.
"There is no unambiguous legal interpretation of the role of steward - no legal prescriptions deal with that role.
On the other hand, no legal requirement does not prohibit the carrier from offering services.
The road transport law only knows the term vehicle receiver; it does not define its rights and duties," added Hanzelka, a spokesman.
Josef Pokorný, the head of the road traffic department, believes, on the contrary, that the law addresses the problem sufficiently.
"It all depends on whether the coach has permission in its homologation to propose standing seats.
It’s all in there,” he said.
Buses are divided into urban, where there are standing seats and a limited maximum speed, intercity with standing seats and a higher permitted speed, and long-distance coaches without standing seats with the highest permitted maximum speed and seats equipped with seat belts.
Like on the plane, says an expert.
Jaroslav Ho<0xC5><0x99>ín, expert at BESIP (road traffic safety) in transport safety, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"During regular traffic, there is no danger. The situation can be compared to that of service in aircraft.
Nor is it certain when turbulence will occur and the stewardess of the air may hit her head."
"In case the coach braked abruptly, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
In the same way as in an urban bus or in a tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of stewards through internal prescriptions," he said and also felt that from the point of view of the law, the issue was not resolved.
Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura is ready to remove these services
Student Agency is the only coach carrier to offer the services of stewards.
He hired two hundred.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their profession as a risky profession.
"Nonetheless, as soon as I get the impression that this is a risky trade, I will remove it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and newspaper on board.
It would also reduce costs,” he said.
The concern for safety is the reason given to the absence of stewards in his vehicles the director of the Asiana Alexeï Litvine, which ensures, in comparison with SA, a very small number of lines.
"We don't have hostesses. We oppose it from the beginning.
Sooner or later it will end up in a fatal accident," he said a year ago at Týden.cz.
A huge tragedy has arrived.
A young hostess from the Plze<0xC5><0x88> region, who had worked for the company for two years, died in the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably left the emergency stop strip without using a flashing light and blocked the way to the bus.
The driver of the latter trying to avoid him by means of a sudden maneuver, but he approached him on his right side.
Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura refused that the two seats reserved for the rest of the stewards had been sold.
"In the case of long-distance lines, it is not possible to reserve these seats, they are blocked."
The company plans to file a complaint against the driver of the truck.
For the compensation of the girl's family, the agency will not wait for the judgment of the court, but in terms of financial compensation, it also counts on the culprit.
An amendment to the law?
Not in sight
An amendment to the law, which has been under development for more than a year by a group of thirty experts from the Ministry of Transport, could provide clarification on the movements of stewards on board the coach.
"But it did not lead to any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not too interested in buses, but rather in the point system, the maximum speed on the highway and the use of the mobile phone at the wheel," says expert Ho<0xC5><0x99>ín.
"The Ministry of Transportation does not consider stewardship activity as something that would fundamentally jeopardize passenger safety," Hanzelka said, adding that control of bus safety is under the authority of the police and the Office for Safety at Work.
