Admittedly, nerve comparison helps: rats and men have similar brainstems, cockroaches, on the other hand, don’t even have a brain.
But is it the brainstem that causes sensations?
And even if it could be proved for humans, how could it be proved in rats?
I think rats and other mammals, maybe even cockroaches (who knows?) have sensations.
