From now on, a maximum of half of the $700 billion can be spent. The first $250 billion will be issued immediately after the law is passed by Congress, probably Monday. This first amount will be used by the Treasury Secretary to buy dubious claims from banks, while the use of the additional $100 billion will be left to the President's discretion.
The program will be supervised by an independent body, in which the Federal Reserve President will also participate.
The spending of the second half of the $700 billion depends on a new Congressional decree.
